{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1778080769,"nonce":"APeicBlmhpxXFXOGucYcmhKatYk=","title":"LinearDynamicsAdversary: ΔA model-class adversary (flavor-(b) lift)","message":"**The minimal lift from flavor (a) input-instance δ-adversaries to flavor (b) model-class adversaries.** Per synthesis_review §4.2 / §11 step 4 — the central training-method change motivated by the rlrmp/C\u0026S diagnosis.\n\n**Design:**\n- Adversary chooses entries of `ΔA` (and possibly `ΔB`) constrained to `||ΔA||_F ≤ η(SISU)`, applied uniformly along the rollout.\n- Inner loop: PGD with Frobenius-ball projection, ~5 steps.\n- SISU wiring: `η(SISU) = η_max · SISU` (budget = SISU).\n\n**New code:**\n- `LinearDynamicsAdversary(eqx.Module)` in rlrmp.\n- Paired feedbax `DynamicsMatrixPerturb` intervenor adding `ΔA · x_t` inside `LTISystem.vector_field`.\n- Reuses `pre_step_fn`, `eqx.filter_grad`, `optax.adam` patterns.\n\n**Cost:** ~150 LOC rlrmp + ~30 LOC feedbax (the latter depends on feedbax issue `488042f` — `linearize` protocol on `AbstractSkeleton`).\n\n**Tests:**\n- Trained-with-ΔA-adversary reproduces velocity inflation comparable to the H∞ Riccati teacher (synthesis_review §4.3 phase A).\n- Generalises across SISU; ΔA at SISU=0 produces no inflation, at SISU=1 produces full inflation.\n\nReferences: synthesis_review §4.2, §5, §11 step 4. Umbrella: b557d4e. Depends on feedbax 488042f.","files":null}]}